Yellow fever, imported - USA from Brazil (02) 961108233248
Date: Fri, 6 Aug 1999 16:18:36 +0200
From: "L'age-Stehr, Johanna" <Lage-StehrJ@rki.de>

The imported case of haemorrhagic fever in a German traveller to
Cote d'Ivoire has been confirmed as yellow fever. The patient died
this morning [6 Aug 1999 in the isolation facility of the Charite
Hospital in Berlin. Yellow fever virus has been isolated from a blood
specimen taken 3 days after typical symptom onset. The last
clinical manifestation was anuria [lack of urine and encephalitis.
We have inspected his vaccination certificate he had used for the
travel and since 1992 and there was no Yellow fever vaccination
registered.
--
